05/05/2004
NEW YORK, United States -- Secretary of State Colin Powell met with Turkish Cypriot Prime Minister Mehmet Ali Talat on Tuesday (4 May), indicating a shift in policy in favour of closer ties with northern Cyprus. The EU has already pledged economic assistance and eased trade regulations for the Turkish Cypriots. The United States and the EU firmly supported the UN plan for the reunification of the island. The blueprint was scuttled when Greek Cypriots voted against it during a referendum last month. The Turkish Cypriots approved the plan. (AFP - 04/05/04)
